Title: BREAKING: Taylor Swift REVEALS Scooter Braun and Scott Borchetta BANNED HER FROM HER OWN MUSIC
Comment:
Dude, this is so messed up. Taylor Swift was the one who wrote that music, sang it, recorded it, and everything else. She's half of the reason why Scott Borchetta is successful in his career (not anymore though. his reputation is as low as his personality now). What did he do while she was working so hard? Sitting around and tell her to keep on going? She sold her masters to him because she had known him for years and she trusted him to keep them safe from the hands of disgusting people. That was when he decided to betray her and hand them over to Scooter, who had been bullying her for years. He could've sold them to someone who Taylor trusted as well, but no, he just had to send them to the bike man. Now here she is, having no rights to even sing or perform the music that she put all of her effort to make. The reactions of the media doesn't help, especially when you know that she has plenty of haters. If someone is as hardworking as Taylor, whether that would be creating your own song or writing a 1,000 page novel, they would know how it feels to have no rights to that product. Unfortunately, they are a pile of uneducated imbeciles who would believe everything they see online. Taylor is hated because she is Taylor, and by the logic of her haters, everything that she does is wrong. Standing up for herself is considered bullying, just like how most teachers react when a student snaps and attacks his bully, but don't care about extreme bullying on it's own. Even if she sacrifices half of her career for someone, it's still going to be considered 'publicity'  by everyone else. 

I can't believe anyone could still support Scott and Scooter after this. It's business, yes, but even that has it's own limits. It's clear that they're intentionally doing this to push her down, not for the name of business itself. Honestly, I can't believe I trusted Scott before all of this. I thought that he was going to be a good man and support Taylor no matter what, but his greed has completely taken over him. He may even be in the point of no return. I hope that Taylor would soon get the respect that she deserves.

Title: We're Getting The Long Version Of All Too Well...| Taylor Swift Tuesday #64
Comment:
First, I was confused by "Combat, I'm ready for combat" both at the beginning and end of "the Archer", as it seemed to 'undo' the progress Taylor shows throughout the song. But I think I figured it out.

In the beginning, she is ready for combat, as that is what she has come to know: relationships end in fights, with lovers, but also with friends ("cause all of my enemies started out friends"). So she keeps her guard up for when his dark side comes out; she even searches for it so it can't take her by surprise, wondering whether, or rather, _how long_ he could stay.

But then she is taken by surprise, as she is alright ("...right, right, right here") and he actually could really stay. And then she is ready for combat, as she knows this relationship is worth the fight.

*Instead of fighting with him over their relationship, she will be fighting together with him for their relationship.*

Because relationships are not just about feelings.
Feelings are how relationships _start._
Communication, cooperation and especially commitment are how relationships _last._

Relationships aren't always easy. You don't just have to fight through the hard times to come out stronger, but healthy relationships require daily effort to not take it for granted. Tell _and show_ your partner your appreciation and affection for them every single day.
Trust me, that kind of strong relationship is worth fighting for.
